<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5> as hell • like hell</xh5><p> <i>as hell</i>—(coll.) extremely; very much <i>(is used to intensify adjectives): </i>Nobody believed him of course, and this made him sore <u>as hell</u>.</p><p> <i>like hell—</i>1. <i>(interj.)</i> not at all; on the contrary <i>(is used to emphatically contradict a statement): </i>“I’ve quite enjoyed it here.” “<u>Like hell</u> I have,” she added under her breath. 2. <i>(coll.)</i> madly; frantically <i>(is used to intensify verbs):</i> I fired when something came into my sights and then turned <u>like hell</u> as something fired at me!</p> </entry>
